 <item> <title>Proposed Rule Links Federal Student Aid to Loan Repayment Rates and Debt-to-Earnings Levels for Career College Graduates</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/proposed-rule-links-federal-student-aid-loan-repayment-rates-and-debt-earnings-levels-career-college-graduates</link>
 <description>The Obama Administration released today its proposed regulations requiring for-profit career colleges to better prepare students for &quot;gainful employment&quot; or risk losing access to federal student aid.  The proposed rules seek to protect students from taking on unsustainable debt they cannot repay and to protect taxpayers from high loan default rates.</description>
